description: If any odd power of 2 ends with k 1's and 2's, they must be the first k elements of this sequence in reverse order.
example: 2^1 ends in 22^5 ends in 322^9 ends in 5122^13 ends in 81922^89 ends in ...562112
author: _David W. Wilson_
extensions: Definition corrected by Gerry Leversha (g.leversha(AT)btinternet.com), Mar 17 2007
